cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.DC

This paper deals with the technical and business structure of DDoS-for-hire services, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the payment infrastructure of these services, which could be categorized under computer networks and communications (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SI). The analysis of leaked and scraped data from major booters could be classified under cryptography and security (cs.CY). Finally, the large-scale payment intervention in collaboration with PayPal could be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
